HEADWORD: lilyturf
<hw>lilyturf</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Asiatic perennial tufted herb
(<spn>Liriope muscari</spn>) with grasslike evergreen foliage and
clusters of dark mauve grapelike flowers; grown as ground
cover.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lily turf, <spn>Liriope muscari</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

